#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2189
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"ENCOUNTER_ZOLTAN_ELITE\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"Though not all Zoltans choose to align with the extreme views of the "
"Duskbringers, that doesn't mean they all appreciate the Federation. A "
"particularly annoyed Zoltan Elite appears to be fed up with tolerating "
"Federation ships and has decided to attack."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2192
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"ENCOUNTER_ZOLTAN_ELITE\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2205
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"At first, you assume the nearby planet isn't anything important - until your"
" Atlas informs you this is actually the location of the Zoltan Capital! "
"Usually these places are better marked, but Ministry government buildings "
"are rarely seen as tourist attractions. You expected the capital to be on "
"the Zoltan Homeworlds, Osmia, but this most certainly isn't any such place."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2209
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Visit the capital."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2211
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"As soon as you approach, it's clear something is eerily wrong. There is "
"barely any activity on the streets near the massive capitol building, and "
"you swear you see several armed patrols stationed outside. Your descent is "
"met with a warning; \"Unregistered foreign vessel - desist at once and leave"
" this zone. This is not a time for complacent intervention from reckless "
"third parties.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2213
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "We aren't a reckless third party - we're Federation."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2215
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"I understand that. My statement still stands. This is a matter of "
"importance for the Ministry and the Ministry alone. Now beat it.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2217
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"LIST_CREW_ZOLTAN_CAPITAL\"]/text"
msgstr "(Ministry Crew) Talk them into allowing you to assist."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2221
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"LIST_CREW_HARMONY\"]/text"
msgstr "(Harmony Crew) Talk them into allowing you to assist."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2225
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"ENERGY_SHIELD\"]/text"
msgstr "(Zoltan Shield) Convince them you are a Zoltan ship."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2229
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[4]/text"
msgstr "Insist on helping anyways."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2231
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[4]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"The Zoltan doesn't bother speaking to you, instead calling on his radio for "
"backup in dispersing you!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2234
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[4]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2240
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice[5]/text"
msgstr "It seems there's no convincing these guys."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2246
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Abide that warning and leave."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2252
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "There's no point in visiting."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2254
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[2]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You have no interest in bothering the Zoltan citizens or sight seeing."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2256
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[2]/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Do something onboard the ship."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2260
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"CAPITAL_OSMIA_RAID\"]/choice[2]/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Do nothing."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2267
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"It seems I have misevaluated your aptitude. I am Allta Foleck, regent and "
"speaker on behalf of Minister Lumei who is not present at this time. As you "
"perhaps have noticed, the capitol has been evacuated, and the city is under "
"lockdown in face of an impending terrorist attack.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2269
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Terrorists? Is it the Duskbringers?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2271
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Allta hesitates, but eventually responds: \"Not quite. We believe they are a"
" more radical, religious sect of the Duskbringers, almost cult like. They "
"have donned masks of hideous three-eyed beasts and wear sacrificial robes, "
"and their only goal is the total annihilation of the Ministry. We have "
"received news that their forces will be arriving soon and they must be "
"apprehended. Death is the only suitable consequence for these acts of "
"terror.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2273
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Agree to stay and help fight the terrorists."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2275
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Not too long later, you catch sight of the first of the terrorist vessels "
"approaching. A decently sized cruiser vessel and very well armed, it looks "
"like this is your chance to earn the Ministry's favor."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2278
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2284
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ASSIST\"]/choice/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Yeah uh, have fun dealing with those guys. We're out of here."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2294
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER\"]/destroyed/text"
msgstr ""
"The strange Zoltan vessel has been vanquished. It causes some damage to the "
"infastructure below when it crashes into the ground, but the Zoltan "
"officials tell you not to worry."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2297
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER\"]/destroyed/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2302
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER\"]/deadCrew/text"
msgstr ""
"The strange Zoltan vessel has been vanquished. It causes some damage to the "
"infastructure below when it crashes into the ground, but the Zoltan "
"officials tell you not to worry."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2305
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER\"]/deadCrew/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2311
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"It seems that, having gotten so low on crew, the ship is now attempting to "
"flee. You don't see this kind of behavior often, but you receive word from "
"Allta. \"Do not let that ship escape! We must ensure the terrorists cannot "
"regroup!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2315
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Keep fighting."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2319
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE\"]/choice[@req=\"FTL_JUMPER\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"(Adv. Navigation) Suggest allowing the ship to escape and track its "
"movements."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2323
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE\"]/choice[@req=\"ADV_SCANNERS\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"(Long-Ranged Scanners) Suggest allowing the ship to escape and track its "
"movements."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2327
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE\"]/choice[@req=\"sensors\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"(Adv. Sensors) Suggest allowing the ship to escape and track its movements."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2332
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE_OFFER\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Absolutely not! You are under direct orders to keep firing on that ship "
"until they are dead! Do NOT attempt to follow them, they are dangerous and "
"must be stopped!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2335
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_ESCAPE_OFFER\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Keep fighting."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2340
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_GOTAWAY\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"The terrorist ship jumps away. You can tell Allta is mad, but he manages to "
"maintain his professional composure despite his wavering voice. \"Very well "
"then. This is not the most optimal outcome, but... we can make do with this."
" The capital has been saved, thanks to your efforts. Heheh...\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2342
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_GOTAWAY\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2346
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_GOTAWAY\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_escape_offer\"]/text"
msgstr "Grab the coordinates of the terrorist ship's new location first."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2348
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_GOTAWAY\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_escape_offer\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"While you speak further with Allta, you proceed to discreetly download the "
"trajectory and coordinates of the strange Zoltan ship. You aren't sure where"
" this will lead, but clearly there's something there the Ministry doesn't "
"want anyone near."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2351
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_GOTAWAY\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_escape_offer\"]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2358
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_WIN\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"You can't help but notice no other ships were present during the attack, and"
" the Zoltan military forces were... very reserved in that they refused to "
"assist you in the fight. Strange, but Allta appears once again to "
"commemorate you. \"I think it goes without saying that without your help, we"
" would not have been able to survive that attack. Allow me to show my "
"generosity to both you and the Federation. Now, feel free to carry on with "
"your mission. I would hate to steal any more of your time.\" You aren't sure"
" where this sudden attitude shift came from, but as promised Allta does "
"deliver a rather large reward, including ship blueprints for a Zoltan "
"cruiser!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2364
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_WIN\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Accept the gift and leave."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2368
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_WIN\"]/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "We have some questions left to ask."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2373
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Oh? Questions? I'm a very busy man I'm afraid. I'll try to entertain your "
"thoughts, but I cannot stick around for long.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2375
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_help\"]/text"
msgstr "Why did none of the other ships help us?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2377
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_help\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"We could see that you had the situation under control. With ships as "
"deadly as theirs, we were not willing to risk our more valuable security "
"teams unless necessary. Many citizens and ground patrols were not given full"
" information on the events that were to transpire to ensure there would be "
"no hysteria. That is all, I hope you were not offended.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2380
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_help\"]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2388
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_attack\"]/text"
msgstr "Why were there no other ships attacking?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2390
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_attack\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"It would seem that we were largely misinformed on the scale of the attack."
" You see, informants can't get everything right all of the time... With this"
" vessel dealt with, I am certain the terrorists will hesitate before making "
"future attacks, but should we ever need help in the future, I suppose we "
"know who to call... Heheh...\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2393
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_attack\"]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2401
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_mask\"]/text"
msgstr "Why were those terrorists' masks so realistic?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2403
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_mask\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"What reasonable man could try and justify the absurd efforts of mentally "
"unstable zealots? Their dedication to their craft is, as some would say, "
"remarkable, but I would sooner call it disturbing. Never fear though, those "
"ghastly creatures are just the same as any Zoltan, and thank goodness for "
"it!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2406
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[@req=\"loc_evidence_os_question_mask\"]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2414
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[4]/text"
msgstr "That's all of our questions."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2416
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_RAID_QUESTIONS\"]/choice[4]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Good, good. You are a very curious individual I see. I appreciate your "
"drive to know more about the galaxy around you, but I must warn you. Try not"
" to go sticking your nose into business you have no part in the future, "
"okay? Bye bye!\" Allta immediately hangs up from the call, and an escort is "
"dispatched to ensure you have a 'safe flight' as you leave the capital."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2422
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER_COLONY\"]/destroyed/text"
msgstr ""
"You've defeated the ship of so-called Osmians. There wasn't much point - the"
" Ministry isn't exactly going to give you a second reward - but at least "
"this mystery is over. Right?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2426
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_OSMIAN_CRUISER_COLONY\"]/deadCrew/text"
msgstr ""
"You've defeated the ship of so-called Osmians. There wasn't much point - the"
" Ministry isn't exactly going to give you a second reward - but at least "
"this mystery is over. Right?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2433
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/beaconType/unvisitedTooltip"
msgstr "Location of the terrorists."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2434
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/beaconType/visitedTooltip"
msgstr "Explored location. Nothing left of interest."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2443
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"As soon as you arrive at the location of the terrorists you're taken aback "
"by the location on your Atlas. THIS is Osmia, homeworld of the Zoltan race. "
"Unlike the capital, which at least had a minor indicator of importance upon "
"arrival, Osmia has no such fanfare. How has the Ministry kept an entire "
"planet hidden from the rest of the Federation - and more importantly, why?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2445
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2447
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"As you follow the coordinates closer to the surface you can see the planet "
"has seen much better days. Similar to most of the homeworlds of galactic "
"empires, it lays in a state of mass disarray, but this is much different. "
"Vegetation is completely absent from almost half of the planet, and that "
"where it can be found it grows erratically. Ancient craters decorate the "
"surface and near them is large amounts of radioactivity. You steer clear of "
"the dead-zones and approach a massive elevated city suspended by several "
"large towers. This is no ruin however - it's bustling with activity."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2449
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2451
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Suddenly, you're stopped by the same ship as before. Their dialect is "
"strange, though close enough to modern Zoltan that your translator fills in "
"the gaps easily. \"Please tell us you have not come to finish us off! "
"Whatever the Ministry has told you is a lie! Please, you must understand, we"
" aren't a threat!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2454
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "You attacked the capital - that seems pretty threatening."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2456
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Look, let me explain! I am Malki, and we are the Osmians. We are not "
"terrorists, I can promise you. We are the last of the few non-transformants "
"that the Ministry could not reach. If you care, I can start from the "
"beginning and explain everything. But I believe you might be of a great help"
" to my people, if you're willing.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2458
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Listen to his explanation."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2462
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "We're in a bit of a hurry here."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2466
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice[3]/text"
msgstr "Don't trust these guys - attack!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2468
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice[3]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You ignore the protests of Malki and silence the ship before moving in to "
"attack."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2471
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUEST\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice[3]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2484
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Okay, okay. Look, why don't we both power down our weapons and meet face "
"to face? If you came this far, you're certainly looking for answers.\" "
"Reluctantly, you agree and you land your ship near a frozen lake. Malki "
"dismounts from his vessel, revealing himself to look the same as the "
"creatures from before."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2486
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "The Ministry said you were disguised Duskbringers."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2488
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"I'm afraid that's a lie. One of many. As you can see, we are not Zoltans "
"in the same sense that you know. Long long before the Federation, all of us "
"Zoltans looked this way. Back then, we were steaming ahead full force into "
"the interstellar era, driven to be the first of many competing nations. But "
"this competition turned to travesty, and nuclear holocaust became imminent. "
"Osmia was annihilated, and the survivors were forced to flee the planet. For"
" almost centuries Osmia was out of our reach, a solemn reminder of our "
"failure.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2490
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2492
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"The lost explorers roamed the surrounding nebula, unable to settle for "
"long without devolving into war once again. However, in those mysterious "
"clouds they found something. At the center of the infamous Great Eye nebula "
"was a monolith that held immense, god-like power. The Zoltans came to "
"worship it, and so it brought them unity. This gave birth to the Illesctrian"
" faith and the Ministry who sought to uphold this new peace. The Ministry, "
"however, was brutal with its enforcement, and to justify its cruelty the "
"leadership constructed an ever-large and rapidly expanding codex of laws no "
"man nor army could ever memorize. Through force they assimilated every last "
"Zoltan colony.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2494
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "But what happened? Why are the Zoltans hard-light now?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2496
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Yes, see, the Great Eye also brought with it the discovery of other, "
"similar tech. Aether, a highly conductive and resistant metal alloy used to "
"forge the ruins around the Eye could be used to create sustainable hard-"
"light generators. This tech enticed the Ministry's top scientists, who saw "
"it as a solution for the Osmia crisis alongside various other tech. Though "
"Aether was used to construct most of Zoltan kind's most infamous technology "
"like our special shields, we also used it to create new part-organic part-"
"mechanical forms to explore Osmia with. This was a success and the explorers"
" were revered as heroes, and many flocked back to recolonize the planet. The"
" current Minister at the time only lived for a little longer until he "
"succumbed to a natural death and was replaced by the new Minister, Lumei.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2498
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Wait, but wasn't this centuries ago? How is Lumei still in charge?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2500
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"This was indeed long ago, but we'll get to the answer for your question "
"soon enough. Under Lumei's leadership the codex was almost doubled in size "
"and enforcement became even stricter. The Osmian explorers, still held high "
"in reverency by the public, were given seats in the Ministry so Lumei could "
"keep them close to him as pawns. Because of the connection between Aether "
"and the Great Eye, these hard-light forms took on a religious significance "
"as well, and so Lumei himself underwent transformation to secure his power. "
"As the technology became better researched soon the wealthy elite, priests, "
"and eventually even the common people were able to afford such procedures. "
"Supremacy of the transformants took hold and, fearful that this divide might"
" create a split between the Zoltans, the Ministry began to normalize and "
"enforce transformancy.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2502
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2504
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Most adamant non-transformants died of natural causes and the newer more "
"'progressive' mindset took hold. All Zoltans over the age of 7 were to be "
"immediately transitioned into hard-light chassis. The only place the "
"Ministry struggled to touch was, ironically, Osmia itself. A group of non-"
"transformants had taken hold there, seizing control of the territory between"
" the wastelands that had survived the initial holocaust. Eventually the "
"Ministry gave up and spent their effort erasing the importance of Osmia from"
" the rest of the Zoltans - something made easier by the recent discovery of "
"other sapient life. And so, that is how the first of we Osmians came to be. "
"The Ministry wants nothing more than for the galaxy to forget we exist and "
"for us to die out naturally.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2506
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_EXPLANATION\"]/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "So, what is it that you needed of us?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2521
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Yes, well I suppose it's best I explain why we were there at the capital "
"then, before I ask of you anything... You see, there are a few of our kind "
"left which have not taken refuge on Osmia. They were captured by the "
"Ministry and kept locked away in a secret laboratory under 'protocol 3', in "
"the case of an unforeseen cataclysmic failure of the hard-light forms. We "
"estimate there's likely several hundred of them locked away from centuries "
"ago - each of them an innocent life, as well as a time capsule for ancient "
"forgotten history. We hoped to storm the Capital and force them to release "
"the captives, but as you can see that didn't work out as planned.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2523
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Whoops. Sorry about that."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2525
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Don't be. We understand your alliance with the Ministry as part of the "
"Federation took precedence. But now, I'm afraid I must ask of you a favor "
"that is not in the interest of that alliance. Our military is not strong "
"enough to take on the vessel guarding the lab, and our only ship capable, "
"you caused quite the damage to. We cannot offer you the same as the Ministry"
" might, so I expect nothing more than your refusal. But if you accept this "
"plea out of the kindness of your heart, then you will forever have the "
"Osmian people's gratitude.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2527
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Agree to rescue the captives."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2529
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Really? I cannot believe this. But I haven't time to thank you any "
"further. I must encourage you to hurry, I cannot say if the Ministry will "
"take action to further protect the specimens in the face of our actions or "
"not. I'll transfer the coordinates immediately. Our transports will be on "
"the way shortly after you arrive. Best of luck. Our people are counting on "
"you.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2534
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Decline."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2536
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_UNLOCK_QUESTION\"]/choice/event/choice[2]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Understandable. At least I can thank you for allowing us to continue to "
"exist as we were. Best of luck on your travels.\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2545
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_ZOLTAN_LAB\"]/destroyed/text"
msgstr ""
"The peacekeepers have been defeated. You expect more reinforcements, but it "
"seems the lab just intends to surrender instead. The Ministry is desperate "
"to hide this truth, but apparently not enough to risk a full-scale war."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2548
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_ZOLTAN_LAB\"]/destroyed/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2553
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_ZOLTAN_LAB\"]/deadCrew/text"
msgstr ""
"The peacekeepers have been defeated. You expect more reinforcements, but it "
"seems the lab just intends to surrender instead. The Ministry is desperate "
"to hide this truth, but apparently not enough to risk a full-scale war."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2556
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//ship[@name=\"SHIP_ZOLTAN_LAB\"]/deadCrew/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2564
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/beaconType/unvisitedTooltip"
msgstr "Location of the secret Ministry Lab."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2565
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/beaconType/visitedTooltip"
msgstr "Explored location. Nothing left of interest."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2576
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"There is zero doubt in your mind this is the place. Just from the immediate "
"sinister appearance, it's clear this is not an ordinary secret base - if "
"there ever was one. According to the Osmians, the security must be tight, "
"and getting any closer without being detected is impossible."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2578
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Pull closer."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2580
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"As soon as you cross a certain threshold, a Peace-keeper vessel activates. "
"It's a cruiser, and therefore no idle threat. \"Entrance to Zone E17 is "
"forbidden. How did you find this place?\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2583
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "No question - time to fight."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2585
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You're done being told what to do by the Ministry. Time to finally give them"
" what they've had coming for a long time."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2588
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2594
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[1]/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Oops sorry, we're lost. We'll leave!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2600
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Leave."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2602
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[2]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You've bitten off more than you can chew this time. The Osmians will need to"
" find someone else to help them."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2604
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[2]/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Do something onboard the ship."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2608
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB\"]/choice[2]/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Do nothing."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2616
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIAN_ARRIVAL\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"Your radar immediately picks up several more pings. You're afraid this means"
" the Zoltans have received reinforcements - but this isn't the case. In "
"fact, it's quite the opposite. The Osmians have arrived, and unlike most of "
"your \"allies\" in conflicts like this, they're actually providing firepower"
" from the sidelines!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2620
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"The Osmian troops, though limited in ships, are plentiful in manpower and "
"storm the lab. The Zoltan scientists surrender. You take note of assorted "
"Engi and even a few workers in Federation garb in the crowd, but you're "
"distracted by Malki. \"Thank you for your help. Though material offers I "
"cannot extend, I can provide your Federation blueprints for our finest "
"warship. We-\" Suddenly, an alarm blares. Something bad is happening!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2624
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2626
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Shortly after the alarm, another warning plays over the stereo. You might be"
" getting tired of all these warnings, but this isn't one to be ignored. "
"\"Evacuate the premises immediately. Nuclear strike imminent.\" Panic "
"immediately breaks out, and your radar detects an approaching warhead. "
"Apparently, in case of emergency, the Ministry rigged this place to destroy "
"itself. If your holopad's estimation is correct, you have 10 minutes before "
"the impact."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2628
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Assist the Osmians in moving the stasis pods."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2630
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Your crew rush over to help, disengaging the pods from their holding "
"compartments and carrying them over to the awaiting Osmian transport "
"vessels. As the timer continues to tick down, you realize there's a much "
"greater issue than the time limit - there isn't enough space for all of the "
"specimens. Malki notices too and is dismayed. \"What will we do now? There "
"isn't enough time for multiple trips!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2632
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "We have to leave them behind!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2636
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"BLUELIST_CREW_STRONG\"]/text"
msgstr "(Strong Crew) Haul some of the pods onto your ship."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2638
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"BLUELIST_CREW_STRONG\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"With the other transports full, the only option is to load the chambers onto"
" your own ship. You bring as many back as possible, but you can't help but "
"notice Malki is still rushing around fruitlessly trying to fit more "
"containers on the other ships."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2641
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[1]/event/choice[@req=\"BLUELIST_CREW_STRONG\"]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Urge him to leave."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2649
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "We've done our part - leave!"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2651
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIA_LAB_WIN\"]/choice/event/choice[2]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You apologize to Malki, but he hardly notices as he's already run off to "
"help move as many stasis chambers as possible. You hurry back to your ship "
"and prepare to leave."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2658
msgid "data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIAN_LEAVE\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"\"Are you insane? We didn't come this far just to leave them behind! We- we "
"have to rescue as many as we can!\" You try to explain there isn't possibly "
"enough time to move them all, but Malki won't listen. Eventually, through "
"force, you manage to drag him back to your ship as the rest of the Osmians "
"flee. Though you weren't able to save all of the specimens and the "
"scientists are doomed, at least all of the Osmians and your crew were able "
"to make it away safely."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2660
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIAN_LEAVE\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_ministry.xml:2662
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_ministry.xml$//event[@name=\"OSMIAN_LEAVE\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"From the distance as you leave the planet behind you can see the flash of "
"the detonation. In grim silence Malki watches, unresponsive. \"I have failed"
" my people. But... I should have known. The Ministry would sooner destroy "
"its heritage than allow its people to see the truth. It's not like it "
"matters to them. If they ever need new specimens they know they can just "
"attack Osmia again. That lab was merely a formality. If news of our raid "
"gets out at all, I'm sure it'll be spun as an accident, though even that is "
"doubtful.\""

